msgid "Catherine Schmidt-Jones, &quot;Major Keys and Scales&quot;, Connexions, December 16, 2009, <a-1>http://cnx.org/content/m10851/2.22/</a-1>. Her work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution License (CC-BY 1.0)."
msgstr ""

#: TheoryHarmony/TheoryHarmony.cpp:229
msgid "Minor natural scales"
msgstr ""

#: TheoryHarmony/TheoryHarmony.cpp:230
msgid "As with major scales, minor scales also share a common pattern of tones and semitones. Let's use again the piano keyboard and play all note names along one octave, but now starting on A. We will get the notes A-B-C-D-E-F-G-A-B:"
